Thank you for reaching back out to us.
I want to set your expectations that it is against our policy to manually increase your rate limit. This is something that is done automatically per the documentation below:
In summary, a businessâ€™s phone number will be upgraded to the next tier if:
Its quality rating is not low, and
The cumulative amount of users it sends notifications to adds up to twice its current messaging limit within a 7-day period.

Once the business reaches this threshold, it will be moved to the next tier. The minimum amount of time that this upgrade can occur is after 48 hours, when the business is sending messages up to their current limit every day. To keep message quality high for end users, we ask that your business follow our tier system for upgrading the messaging capacity of its phone numbers.
Regards, Kai Meta support for business messaging

Kindly note that the purpose of this ticket was to increase the messaging limit for my number since i was following your guidelines for more than a month and nothing has changed for my number till now so kindly increase my messaging limit regarding my number
Upon checking, it turns out that it is against our policy to manually increase your rate limit. This is something that is done automatically per the documentation below:
In summary, a businessâ€™s phone number will be upgraded to the next tier if:
Its quality rating is not low, and
The cumulative amount of users it sends notifications to adds up to twice its current messaging limit within a 7-day period.

Once the business reaches this threshold, it will be moved to the next tier. The minimum amount of time that this upgrade can occur is after 48 hours, when the business is sending messages up to their current limit every day. To keep message quality high for end users, we ask that your business follow our tier system for upgrading the messaging capacity of its phone numbers.
